Edison Only Bidder for Completing Serb Kolubara Plant, Beta Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-05-20T16:03:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/edison-only-bidder-for-completing-serb-kolubara-plant-beta-says.html
Italy’s  Edison SpA (EDN)  submitted the sole
bid for building  Serbia ’s coal-fired Kolubara B,  Beta  newswire
said, citing the state-run power company  Elektroprivreda Srbije .  Financial details of the offer for “strategic
partnership” with EPS in developing the 700 megawatt plant
southwest of Belgrade, whose construction began in 1988, were
not disclosed and Serbia’s dominant power producer is to respond
to the offer by May 31, the report said.  The cost of completing Kolubara B and building another 700-
megawatt facility, at the EPS’s Nikola Tesla thermo plant, has
been estimated at 1.6 billion euros ($2.27 billion), according
to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
